         <abstract>
            <p>An energy-preserving, linearly implicit finite difference scheme is presented for approximating solutions to the periodic Cauchy problem for the one-dimensional Zakharov system of two nonlinear partial differential equations. First-order convergence estimates are obtained in a standard "energy" norm in terms of the initial errors and the usual discretization errors.</p>
          </abstract>
